Bank of America Long-Term Senior Debt Cut to Baa1 by Moody’s

-- B y   V i v e k   S h a n k a r
-- 
2011-09-21T16:32:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/bank-of-america-long-term-senior-debt-cut-to-baa1-by-moody-s.html
Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  had its long-
term senior debt rating cut to Baa1 from A2 and short-term debt
cut to Prime-2 from Prime-1 by Moody’s Investors service.   The long-term deposit ratings of Bank of America NA were
downgraded to A2 from Aa3 and its short-term rating was affirmed
at Prime-1. The outlook on the long-term ratings remains
negative, Moody’s said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vivek Shankar at 
 vshankar3@bloomberg.net  